    <p>Sin­ga­pore sprinter Shanti Pereira, who holds the 100m and 200m national records, yes­ter­day launched a chil­dren’s book com­mem­o­rat­ing her jour­ney to­wards the 200m SEA Games ti­tle in 2015. The book, ti­tled Go Shanti Go, is co-au­thored by her sis­ters Va­lerie, 30, and Shobi, 35, and il­lus­trated by Si­enny Sep­ti­bella. The book is avail­able at www.goshantigo.com for $14.90.</p>

